@node tips "hottips"
                                 @{b}H o t T i p s@{ub}
                                 =============

0.create a encryped .zip file on your PC/Amiga/MAC/Linux with winZip or other zip utils 
 .& try to recover with ZipRecoVer on Amiga.
 .ziprecover combination .


1.Take a note to file size which you are try'ing to recover, so you dont have to
 .check every file in Recv_Files/

2.if you have not typed at RecoVer from, you'l get output as numbers
 .note that number & open Wrdlist file go down/count to that number yea(password found) 
 .also works if you did type lets say myfile then you'l get ouput as myfile12.

3.When Generate'ing PassWords to speedup Switch off 2User[X] to X.

4.if you dont want aaaa's before Passwords Switch that to aaaaa[X]

5.there more i just leave that to users to play around with it. 

@endnode

@node Install "Installation"
                                 @{b}Installation@{ub}
                                ==============
Using Install to install
------------------------

1.double click on Install Icon

2.Click On Install

3.Select Destination by double click on the disk icon 
 .(dont touch the file name keep it as ZipRecoVer)
 .just goto drawers where you want to install & will make a drawer called ZipRecoVer/
 .than Click On [OK] button & click on Go Big right [>] icon.
 .thats all.

to unInstall
------------

0.make sure it assigned. (if not just double click on AssigneMee Icon)

1.same as Install but instead of Install click on unInstall button

2.dont use disk icon (not needed) 

3.reboot your amiga goto where Ziprecover were it used to be kept delete if any files
 .still remains.

installing without installer.
-----------------------------
Copy  Zip-RecoVer Folder to Where ever You Want But Keep  all the files, 
In Same Drawer.

assign Ziprecover: your hd:

exmple..
assign Ziprecover: programs:tmp/ZipRecover/


funzip is part of gnu world...

funzip needed to perform > Try after all done option..
copy funzip to sys:c/ (auto installer does it for you)


before you run ZipRecoVer 
-------------------------
1.you need to assign by double clicking on AssignMe Icon (after it has installed)
 .but you can also edit s:user-startup (then you dont need to use AssignMe icon) 

             
@endnode



@node usage "usage"
                                 @{b}Usage@{ub}
                              ==============

   
Basic Usage Of Zip-RecoVer Click & Go But Not That Simple.

1.click on filename disk icon ziprecover:ZipBox/yourfilename.zip

2.click on Wordlist icon Ziprecover:WrdBox/pwlist or download wordlist from internet

3.click on try after all done button (O) (must have funzip in your sys:c/funzip)

4.type the file name you want to recover from yourfilename.zip & return.

5.ready click on right arrow go button..
5.1 if you are luck you'l get window with password printed out for you..
5.2 plus goto ziprecover:Recv_Files/ see if file recovered.
5.3 also open ziprecover:Recv_Pass/Possible_Wrds if any listed if not?
5.4 get some good (Wordlist) on the net & try it 
if no success wait until ZipRecover_Pro to shape up..mean time check www.webmem.net

                               @{b}MKWords ßeta@{ub}
                              ==============

Gen Words v1(MKWords) Generates Words.(Quick addon to ziprecover by saygi)

first time length needs to be 3 there after 0-8 to perform..
if you are going to use Lower[O] make sure rest needs to be [X or ?]
selected option is [O] & not selected options are [X].

Basic usage.

1.set length to 3 for first time.
2.set Lower[O]
3.2User[O or X] if you want to see the progress switch that to [O].
3.please note if you dont have 040/060/ppc amigas 2User[O] is to Slooow.

4.Save as any filename you want (if you dont type any then saveout as def.list)
5.click on big right arrow icon to start..
5.before you do that make sure you have some hardisk space to cover all.
5.there no stop button to exit so you have to wait until progressing done.

 
 

@endnode

